# Final polish of text documentation

1. HCDE designs the solutions to global challenages by tailoring technology to human needs and interests, and its main duty is an investigation on the interaction of people with technology and technical development. (1)
2. After getting the degree of HCDE, people will get the jobs called UX/UI designer/researcher. These job duties are enhancement of customer satisfaction and loyalty by improving the usability, ease of use, and pleasure provided in the interaction between the customer and the product. (2)
3. The average pay for a User Experience Designer is $72,000 per year. IT companies such as IBM Corp, Amazon, Microsoft and Google are likely looking for UX/UI designers as interaction of techonolgy and people considers important. (3)
4. User Experience Design is the process of development and improvement of quality interaction between a user and all facets of a company, but User Interface Design is responsible for the transference of a brand’s strengths and visual assets to a product’s interface as to best enhance the user’s experience. (2)
5. UX/UI process is not hard as anyone can easily approach and access ux/ui process. Actually, people are probably doing some of ux/ui process already, even though people don't notice it. (4)

